   "source": [
    "### PartialRankerMin"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Experiments with finding the partial rank with minimum possible number of ranks.  In order to follow, please refer to Methodology 3 in the paper. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Experiment 3\n",
    "\n",
    "Consider again the data from the previous section for which Methodology2 did not find the partial ranking with the least number of ranks. Recall, **10 objects** are created, each with **3 measurement values** sampled from 2 different normal distributions that **are well-separated**.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from partial_ranker import MeasurementsSimulator, MeasurementsVisualizer\n",
    "\n",
    "n1 = [0.2, 0.02]\n",
    "n2 = [0.3,0.02]\n",
    "M5 = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(5):\n",
    "    M5['t{}'.format(i)] = n1\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(5,10):\n",
    "    M5['t{}'.format(i)] = n2\n",
    "    \n",
    "ms = MeasurementsSimulator(M5,seed=512)\n",
    "ms.measure(reps=3)\n",
    "measurements = ms.get_measurements()\n",
    "\n",
    "mv = MeasurementsVisualizer(measurements)\n",
    "fig = mv.show_measurements_boxplots(scale=0.5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**The Partial Ranks according to Methodology 3**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{0: {'t0', 't1', 't2', 't3', 't4'}, 1: {'t5', 't6', 't7', 't8', 't9'}}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from partial_ranker import QuantileComparer, Method,PartialRanker\n",
    "\n",
    "cm = QuantileComparer(measurements)\n",
    "cm.compute_quantiles(q_max=75, q_min=25)\n",
    "cm.compare()\n",
    "pr = PartialRanker(cm)\n",
    "pr.compute_ranks(Method.Min)\n",
    "pr.get_ranks()"
   ]
  }
 ],
